A joyful New Year to you all out there! Happy happy holidays! I don’t know about you, but I miss seeing my friends. Somehow since the beginning of COVID-19, you just don’t see them enough, so that’s my hope for the New Year! As well as peace on 🌍, particularly in the Ukraine 🇺🇦! Wishing you all a Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year! 
Lots of love, MD

What an extraordinary couple they were. I miss them both so much. This month marks the 3rd anniversary of Dad’s passing in 2020. I want to let everybody know about the incredible archive collection that we put together on Dad’s career, his life, and his philanthropy, the incredible love affair between the two of them. If you have an interest or want to be reminded, please go to The Douglas Foundation website and you can find a way to look at the archives, which is a tremendous memory of what an extraordinary couple they were and how much they accomplished. I guess most importantly, how much they gave to other people! 

Thank you for @ardonbarhama for your hard work and efforts in putting together the Archive. Please click the link in my Instagram bio to access and check out The Douglas Archive. Thank you! Michael
Happy Valentine’s Day to my darling Catherine! I love you so much @catherinezetajones ❤️ #ValentinesDay
Today marks the 30th anniversary of #FallingDown. It was a great film to make and one of my favorite roles in my career! #30years

Hello everyone! When you get to New York there’s a lot of wonderful amazing things to see and do. I would encourage everyone, if you haven’t been yet, to come down to the @911memorial. Really one of the most powerful memories and statements about peace that you could ever find. Wishing you all well! Peace! MD

As a UN Messenger of Peace, I celebrate the new International Day for Disarmament and Non-Proliferation and Awareness.
 
Disarmament efforts play a vital role in contributing to enhancing peace and security, preventing and ending armed conflicts, and curbing human suffering caused by weapons.
 
Join me! @unitednations @unitednations_oda 
 
#IDDNPA #5March #Disarmament

Let’s #StepUp4Disarmament!
 
Next week on Tuesday, August 29 is the International Day against Nuclear Tests.
 
This day was established by the @unitednations in 2009 to raise awareness about the devastating impacts of nuclear weapons testing on human lives and the environment.

To mark the occasion, join me and hundreds of young people around the world in a global walk on August 29 to raise awareness and take action! Please click the link in my bio to register now! @unitednations @unitednations_oda @youth4disarmament 
 
#StepUp4Disarmament #Youth4Disarmament #IDANT 
#InternationalDayAgainstNuclearTests

I agree with @unitednations Secretary-General @antonioguterres message! 

“On this United Nations Day, let us commit with hope and determination to build the better world of our aspirations.

Let us commit to a future that lives up to the name of our indispensable organization.

We are a divided world. We can and must be united nations.” 

@unitednations @unpeacekeeping #UNDay

Over 200 men, women, children, and babies have been taken hostage by Hamas terrorists. Noam Avigdori is 12 years old and we need to bring her home now! 

These innocents are currently being trapped within the Gaza strip, and no one has any idea when or if they will be returned home – not even their families.

From infants as young as 9 months, to elderly Holocaust survivors, they’ve been brutally ripped away from their loved ones.

We need to bring them back! @bringhomenow @ccfpeace #BringThemHomeNow
